                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.19908/2605.19908v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Conceptual overview.Left: The pretrained language model encodes stylistic features at every layer, regardless of fine-tuning.Center: Two scoring mechanisms read out these features differently. Mean pooling averages all tokens into a single vector. Late interaction (LI)(Khattab and Zaharia,2020)compares tokens directly.Right: Causal intervention reveals that the scoring mechanism determines where the encoder consolidates authorship signal. Mean pooling forces early consolidation whileMaxSim\\mathrm{MaxSim}allows for late consolidation.",
